label: uncl8169
comment: Code indicating whether an object is full or empty.

values.label: More than one quarter volume available
values.comment: Indicates that there is more than a quarter of the volume available.

values.label: More than half volume available
values.comment: Indicates that there is more than a half of the volume available.

values.label: More than three quarters volume available
values.comment: Indicates that there is more than three quarters of the volume available.

values.label: Empty
values.comment: Indicates that the object is empty.

values.label: Full
values.comment: Indicates that the object is full.

values.label: No volume available
values.comment: Indicates that there is no space available in the object.

values.label: Full, mixed consignment
values.comment: Indicates that the equipment is fully loaded, and includes a number LCL (Less Than Container Load) consignments.

values.label: Full, single consignment
values.comment: Indicates that the container is fully loaded with a single FCL (Full Container Load) consignment.

values.label: Part load
values.comment: Container represents part of a consignment declared on a single Customs declaration (i.e. the Customs declaration covers more than one container).

values.label: Part load mixed consignments
values.comment: Container represents part of the consignment declared on a single Customs declaration with the remainder being in other containers. Other goods, related to other declarations, are also in the container.

values.label: Single invoiced load
values.comment: Merchandise within a container/package covered by a single invoice.

values.label: Multi invoiced load
values.comment: Merchandise within a container/package covered by more than one invoice.

values.label: Full load, multiple bills
values.comment: A container representing a consignment of goods for one consignee with multiple bill of lading numbers.
